    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-12-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-12-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="48"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d48">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.00/740.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador to Japan</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-12-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 7, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I am authorized by the Minister for Foreign Affairs to say that if hostilities
                    continue and become aggravated the Japanese Government may consider intervention
                    to be necessary.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
